  "prompt": "I am graduating in may 2018, should I apply for CDS 1 of 2017?",
  "response": "If you were graduating in May 2018, here are some key points to consider for the CDS (Combined Defense Services) exam:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- Graduation date matters for age and education requirements\n- You would be eligible to apply for CDS exam based on your upcoming graduation\n\n2. CDS 1 of 2017 (Retrospective):\n- If this exam was already conducted before your graduation, you would NOT be eligible\n- Typically, you need to have completed/be about to complete your graduation at the time of the exam\n\n3. CDS 1 of 2018:\n- This would be the most appropriate exam for you\n- Align with your graduation timeline\n- Check the specific notification for exact eligibility dates\n\n4. Recommended Steps:\n- Verify the exact date of the CDS 1 2017 exam\n- Check the official UPSC notification for precise eligibility criteria\n- If the exam was before your graduation, wait for the next cycle\n\n5. Age Limit:\n- Generally 20-24 years for various entries\n- Confirm the specific age requirements for CDS\n\nBest advice: Wait for the CDS 1 2018 exam, which would match your graduation timeline.",
